error.
.SH Description
\f[CR]SHCrossPowerSpectrumDensity\f[R] will calculate the cross\-power
spectral density of two functions expressed in real 4\-pi normalized
spherical harmonics.
For a given spherical harmonic degree \f[CR]l\f[R], this is explicitly
calculated as:
.PP
\f[CR]cspectrum(l) = Sum_{i=1}\(ha2 Sum_{m=0}\(hal cilm1(i, l+1, m+1) * cilm2(i, l+1, m+1) / (2l + 1)\f[R].
